rus pandemic]].\n\n== Offseason ==\n\n=== Departures ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n!Name \n!Number\n!Pos.\n!Height \n!Weight \n!Year\n!Hometown\n!Reason\n|-\n| Jamarius Burton\n| 2\n| G\n| 6'3\"\n| 200\n| {{sort|2|Sophomore}}\n| [[Charlotte, North Carolina]]\n| Transferred to [[Texas Tech Red Raiders men's basketball|Texas Tech]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Marty|first1=Sean|date=13 April 2020|title=Former Shocker guard Jamarius Burton commits to Texas Tech|url=https://thesunflower.com/50592/sports/former-shocker-guard-jamarius-burton-commits-to-texas-tech/|publisher=thesunflower.com|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| DeAntoni Gordon\n| 3\n| F\n| 6'7\"\n| 210\n| {{sort|1|Freshman}}\n| [[Mobile, Alabama]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n| Erik Stevenson\n| 10\n| G\n| 6'3\"\n| 198\n| {{sort|2|Sophomore}}\n| [[Lacey, Washington]]\n| Transferred to [[Washington Huskies men's basketball|Washington]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Allen|first1=Percy|title=Washington gets commitment from Wichita State transfer and Lacey native Erik Stevenson|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/sports/uw-husky-basketball/washington-gets-commitment-from-wichita-state-transfer-and-lacey-native-erik-stevenson|publisher=[[Seattle Times]]|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Noah Fernandes\n| 11\n| G\n| 5'11\"\n| 172\n| {{sort|1|Freshman}}\n| [[Mattapoisett, Massachusetts]]\n| Transferred to [[UMass Minutemen basketball|UMass]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kurie|first1=Brendan|title=Noah Fernandes returns to home state with transfer to UMass|url=https://www.southcoasttoday.com/sports/20200319/noah-fernandes-returns-to-home-state-with-transfer-to-umass|publisher=southcoasttoday.com|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Jaime Echenique\n| 21\n| C\n| 6'11\"\n| 258\n| {{sort|4|Senior}}\n| [[Barranquilla|Barranquilla, Colombia]]\n| Graduated\n|-\n| Tate Busse\n| 32\n| G\n| 6'2\"\n| 185\n| {{sort|1|Freshman}}\n| [[St. Francis, Kansas]]\n| Walk-on; transferred\n|-\n| Asbj\u00f8rn Midtgaard\n| 33\n| C\n| 7'0\"\n| 